column2: Guys, hurry up! The flight leaves in four hours! It could take time to\nget a taxi! There could be traffic! The plane could leave early! When we get to London,\nthere could be a line at customs! Come on!! (She runs back to her apartment.)'
Six-hour trip to London. That\xc2\x92s a lot of Monica.'
Passport, check! (As she puts away each item, she says check.) Camera,\ncheck! Traveller\xc2\x92s cheques, check! '
Who are you saying "check" too?'
Myself. Y\xc2\x92know for remembering to pack a thing. Yeah, you do a good\nthing, you get a check! (pause) My mom does it, I never realized it was weird.'
Yeah, my mom used to put her head in the oven. Well, actually, she only\ndid it the one time. But it was pretty weird.'
(entering) Hey!'
Hey!'
Hey! Are you ready yet?'
Yep! You got the tickets?'
Oh! Got \xc2\x91em right here, (Pats his coat pocket) check!'
It\xc2\x92s all London, baby! Here we go. (He takes a picture of a less than\nenthused Chandler and starts towards the girls\xc2\x92 apartment.)'
You got your passport?'
Yeah, in my third drawer on my dresser. You don\xc2\x92t want to lose that.'
Ohh!! (Runs to his room.)'
There it is.'
Okay, if you need the vacuum, it\xc2\x92s in my closet on the left-hand\nside. Ah, the garbage bags are next to the refrigerator\xc2\x85'
Okay, okay, but Rachel\xc2\x92s gonna be here too, can\xc2\x92t I just ask\nher this stuff?'
Yeah, okay, give that a try!'
(entering, with Joey) All right! Let\xc2\x92s do it!'
Woo-hoo!!'
Yeah, cheerie-o! '
London baby!'
Okay, \xc2\x91cause that\xc2\x92s not gonna get annoying.'
(louder) London baby!!'
Hey, y\xc2\x92know what? I was wrong.'
Well, we\xc2\x92re all here! I guess we should get going!'
Ohhh, I wanna come over there and give you a hug and wish you luck on\nyour wedding, but I don\xc2\x92t\xc2\x97can\xc2\x92t get up.'
Oh, I\xc2\x92ll-I\xc2\x92ll come hug you.'
Great! Yeah, could you bring me the newspaper?'
Yeah. (He does so and Phoebe hugs him.)'
Oh, have a great wedding!'
Thanks.'
Oh, hey, Chandler I wanna hug you too!'
Hey! (Trots over)'
Oh, and great! You might as well bring me my book, it\xc2\x92s on the\ncounter in your apartment.'
Oh. (Goes and gets Phoebe\xc2\x92s book as Rachel comes in from her\nroom.)'
(to Rachel) So, we\xc2\x92re off.'
Have fun!'
Thanks! (They hug.) Ugh, I can\xc2\x92t believe you\xc2\x92re not gonna be\nthere!'
Oh, I know.'
So-so come! Why don\xc2\x92t you come?'
What?!'
To London! Come to London. Please? It\xc2\x92ll mean so much to me.'
Yeah, well, I gotta work, I\xc2\x92m sorry.'
Why-why can\xc2\x92t you take a couple of days off?'
Because, I can\xc2\x92t! Ross, I told you, no. I can\xc2\x92t.'
This is my wedding.'
All right, y\xc2\x92know what? We really are late! Let\xc2\x92s go!\nLet\xc2\x92s go! Let\xc2\x92s go!!'
Fine. You\xc2\x92ll-you\xc2\x92ll watch it on video when we get back.'
(entering, with Phoebe\xc2\x92s book.) Here you go Phoebe! Here you go\nPhobo! Phewbedo! Phaybobo.'
(laughs) Thank you.'
Thank you. (She pats him on his head.)'
All right, let\xc2\x92s go! Bye, Pheebs!'
Bye, Pheebs!'
London baby!! (And Rachel slowly closes the door, sadly.)'
Oh, do you need a hug? You don\xc2\x92t have to bring me anything!'
Come on! Do something!'
I am, I\xc2\x92m ignoring you.'

Okay, here! (Gives him the camera.) I wanna be the on camera guy. All\nright, first stop, Westminster Abbey. (Joey folds out his "pop-up" map of\nLondon. All of the major landmarks pop-up like in a pop-up book.)'
Oh, what the hell is that?'

It\xc2\x92s London, baby! All right, the hotel\xc2\x92s here. (Points to the\nmap.) Wait. No, we wanna go\xc2\x85 No. I know. (Sets the map down.) I\xc2\x92m gonna have to\ngo into the map. (So Joey literally steps into the map.)'
Okay, if you see a little version of me in there? Kill it!'
I got it! (Picks up the map and starts walking.) Here we go.'
Okay. Listen-listen, we\xc2\x92re not gonna have to walk this way the\nentire time are we?'
Shhh! (Pause) Man, you made me lose it! (He goes into the map again.)'

\xc2\x85and that was all before 10 o\xc2\x92clock. The caterer rang and said
it was going to be Chicken Kiev instead of Chicken Tarragon. And then the florist phoned
to say there aren\xc2\x92t any tulips. Oh, and the chilliest has carpel-tunel syndrome.
We\xc2\x92re not gonna be\xc2\x85'
Whoa-whoa-whoa! Emily, (Gives her the time-out signal.) honey, okay?'
Well, up yours too!'
What?! No! No! That\xc2\x92s-that\xc2\x92s time-out!'
Sorry.'
Sweetie, you gotta relax. Everything\xc2\x92s gonna be great, okay? Come on.\nCome on.'
Chicken Kiev?'
Um-hmm! Doesn\xc2\x92t that sound delicious at the last minute?'

Yeah, y\xc2\x92know, but something like salmon which would be so much more\nelegant than the chicken. And, you wouldn\xc2\x92t have to worry about the salmonella. (Ross\npushes her.) So, I can\xc2\x92t wait to see this place you\xc2\x92re getting married!'
Yeah. Yeah. Yes, this place is beautiful. Emily\xc2\x92s parents got married\nhere.'

I still can\xc2\x92t believe they\xc2\x92re tearing it down. It really is the\nmost lovely building you\xc2\x92ll ever see. I mean it\xc2\x92s over\xc2\x85 (She stops\nsuddenly, when she sees that demolition has already started.) Oh my God!'
It\xc2\x92s nice.'
Oh. Oh. (She starts running towards the building.)'
(running in, with Ross) Oh. Oh my God. How can this be happening? What\nare we going to do?'
It\xc2\x92s all right! Everything\xc2\x92s gonna be all right.'
How\xc2\x92s it gonna be all right?!'
Uh-huh, I see that.'
(entering) Okay, I talked to the guy with the shovel and I found out\nwhat happened. '
What? What?'
They torn it down a few days early.'
All right! Westminster Abbey! Hands down, best Abbey I\xc2\x92ve ever seen.\nHey! (Pushes Chandler in front of the camera.) Okay. What do you think of the Abbey,\nChandler?'
I think it\xc2\x92s great. It\xc2\x92s great. Y\xc2\x92know, they\xc2\x92re\nthinking of changing the name of this place.'
Really? To what?'
To Put the Camera Away!!!'
Man, you are Westminster Crabby. (He starts chasing Chandler\ntowards the Abbey.)'
Oh. Oh.'
Oh, honey! Don\xc2\x92t get up! What do you need?'
Oh, no. Oh, nothing.'
Come on! I am here to take care of you! What do you need? Anything.'
Okay, I have a wedgie.'
Okay, that is all you.'
So-so, what do you want for lunch?'
Oh, I don\xc2\x92t know. I guess we have to eat.'
Yeah, I do. What\xc2\x92s the matter?'
I\xc2\x92m just bummed about the way I left things with Ross. I\nshouldn\xc2\x92t have lied to him about having to work. He seemed so mad at me.'
Eh, don\xc2\x92t be so hard on yourself. If someone I was still in love\nwith was getting married\xc2\x85'
(interrupting) Still in love with?! '
Yeah!'
I\xc2\x92m not in love with Ross!'
Oh. No. No. Good! Yeah, me neither.'

Phoebe, I\xc2\x92m going to Ross\xc2\x92s wedding because he is my
ex-boyfriend and that would be really uncomfortable. Not because, I\xc2\x92m still in
love with him! I mean, hey, y\xc2\x92know, I like Ross as much as the next guy, y\xc2\x92know?
Clearly I have feelings for him, but feelings don\xc2\x92t mean love! I mean, I still
have loving feelings for Ross. Yeah! But, I have, I have continuing feelings of love, but
that doesn\xc2\x92t mean that-that I\xc2\x92m still in love with him. Y\xc2\x92know? I-I have
sexual feelings for him, but I do love him\xc2\x97Ohh! Oh my God! Oh my\xc2\x97why
didn\xc2\x92t you tell me?!!'
We thought you knew!'
We?!'
Yeah, we all know! We talk about it all the time!'
You all know? Does Ross know?'
Oh no, Ross doesn\xc2\x92t know anything.'
Oh, I can not believe you didn\xc2\x92t tell me!'
Well, because we thought you knew!! It\xc2\x92s so obvious! God, that\nwould be like telling Monica, "Hey, you like things clean."'
Hey!'
So, what are you guys in the market for? We\xc2\x92ve got uh, scarves,\ntulip post cards...'
Check this out? Huh? (Joey has this big tall hat with a British flag on\nthe front of it.) Yeah. That\xc2\x92s the stuff. What do you think?'
Well, I don\xc2\x92t have to buy that, "I\xc2\x92m with stupid"\nT-shirt anymore.'
Well, I like it. Here you go. (He pays for the hat.)'
All right, look, you\xc2\x92re not really gonna buy that are you?\nDon\xc2\x92t you think you\xc2\x92ve embarrassed me enough for one day?'
Oh, I embarrass you? '
How can I answer that when I\xc2\x92m pretending I don\xc2\x92t know you?'
He\xc2\x92s just jealous. You\xc2\x92ll fit right in; all Londoners wear\nthem!'
Oh really? Then how come no one here is wearing them?'
(looks around) They\xc2\x92re all tourists.'
All right, look, if you insist on wearing that, in public,\ny\xc2\x92know, you\xc2\x92re gonna spend the rest of the afternoon all by yourself.'
Oh yeah? (Puts the hat on.) If you\xc2\x92re gonna make me choose between\nyou and the hat? I choose the hat.'
Good choice.'
Thanks.'
Okay, wait. All right, that\xc2\x92s it, okay, I\xc2\x92m out of here. I\nam not going to be embarrassed anymore! (He trips over a box, falls into a flower stand\nand walks away trying to be cool.)'
Hello?'
Hey! I just spoke to your dad, and you know what? He seems to think\nwe\xc2\x92ll be able to find a new place for the wedding.'
We don\xc2\x92t have to.'
Whoa-whoa-what? You found a place?'
No. But, Monica and I were talking, and-and I was so upset about the hall\nbeing knocked down, and she suggested that we put the wedding off for a bit.'
She said what?'
She said, "If I\xc2\x92m not gonna be happy getting married somewhere\nthat we find in a day, well then we should just postpone it."'

Postpone it? Emily, do you think Monica realises how much our parents
spent on this wedding? Do you my sister\xc2\x92s teeny-tiny little brain comprehends that
people took time out of their lives to fly thousands of miles to be here, huh? (He puts
his pants on backwards.) This isn\xc2\x92t right.'
I realize that people are going to be disappointed. But, I\xc2\x92m sure\nthey\xc2\x92ll come back when we can do it right.'
I can\xc2\x92t ask people to do that? Would you ask people to do that?\n(Holds out his pants)'

Don\xc2\x92t you point your pants at me! (She throws them on the floor.) We\nhave no choice! Anywhere that\xc2\x92s half-decent would\xc2\x92ve be booked months ago, Ross\ndon\xc2\x92t you understand? This is our wedding I\xc2\x92m talking about.'
The only thing I understand is; postponing it is not an option. This is\nwhen we\xc2\x92re getting married.'
So what are you saying? It\xc2\x92s now or never?'
No. I\xc2\x92m saying it\xc2\x92s now. (He starts putting on his pants,\nbackwards again.)'
Or?'
There\xc2\x92s no \xc2\x91or\xc2\x92 in mind. What is wrong with these pants?!!'

It\xc2\x92s not the pants. It\xc2\x92s you that is backwards. And if, and if\nyou don\xc2\x92t understand how important this is to me, well then, perhaps we\nshouldn\xc2\x92t get married at all! (She storms out.)'

(chasing her, trying to zip up his pants. His got them on right now.) No,\nwait! Emily! No, wait, stop! Emily, please\xc2\x97(He catches something important in the\nzipper and howls like a little boy and falls to the floor.)'
Hey!'
(depressed) Hi.'
So, did shopping make you feel any better about Ross?'
Manhattan does not have enough stores.'
Well, I think I can help you get over him.'
You can?'
Yeah. I just need you to bring me some photos of Ross.'
Um-hmm.'
And a small piece of chocolate.'
Okay.'
And a glass of tepid water. (She gathers up all of these things.)'
Ooh, is this one of those things where you throw it in a bag with some\ngraveyard dirt and hang it from a north-facing tree?'

Uh, only if you have the hiccups too. Yeah, the pictures are for you,
the water and the chocolate is for me. I just didn\xc2\x92t feel like getting up. Okay,
I\xc2\x92m gonna show you a picture of Ross. Okay? And you\xc2\x92re going to remember all of
the bad things about him. All right? Really focus on his flaws.'
I can do that. I certainly did it when we were going out.'

Okay. Umm, before we get started, I just wanna say for the record that I
love Ross, I think he\xc2\x92s such a great guy. Here. (Hands her the picture, Rachel grabs
it out of her hand.) Okay, now, close your eyes. And imagine that you\xc2\x92re with Ross
okay and imagine that you\xc2\x92re kissing him. And you\xc2\x92re-you\xc2\x92re running your
hands all over his body. And then you run your hands through his hair, but eew-oh gross
it\xc2\x92s some kind of grease, it\xc2\x92s\xc2\x97uck! Hah?'
I don\xc2\x92t know, his uh, his hair never really bothered me that much,\nand y\xc2\x92know it was always more crunchy than it was greasy.'
Okay, this is going to be harder than I thought. Umm, let\xc2\x92s try\nsome uh, aversion therapy.'
Okay.'
Okay?'
All right.'
So uh, now look at the picture\xc2\x85'
Okay.'
All right, and umm\xc2\x85 (She grabs the picture and smacks her in the\nhead.) '
Ow!'
Okay, how do you feel now?'
Well, I like you less!'
Hey.'
Hey. (He nods at the hat.)'
Oh. (Takes off the hat.) Sorry!'

No-no-no, y\xc2\x92know what? I really shouldn\xc2\x92t have said that you\nwere embarrassing me, I mean that really wasn\xc2\x92t cool. And if it makes you feel any\nbetter, I\xc2\x92ve had a really lousy day.'
Me too.'
Yeah?'
Noo!! I\xc2\x92ve had the best day ever! Dude, check this out!'
(entering) Hey!'
Sh-shh-shh! (He motions for her to watch something he has taped.)'
(on tape) Okay, so say hi to my friend and tell him that you like the hat.\n'
(Yep, Sarah, the Duchess of York) Okay, so umm, what\xc2\x92s your\nfriend\xc2\x92s name?'
(on tape) Oh, Chandler.'
Hi Chandler! (Waves) '
That\xc2\x92s\xc2\x85 That\xc2\x92s was\xc2\x85'
Oh my God!'
That\xc2\x92s Fergie baby!!'
Joey says you don\xc2\x92t really like his hat, but I think it\xc2\x92s\nkinda dashing.'
How did you? How? How?'
Well, I was trying to figure out how to get to Buckingham Palace, right?\nSo, I\xc2\x92m in my map and-and\xc2\x85(Ross enters) Hey!'
Hey!'
Hi. I understand you had a little talk with Emily.'
(laughs) Yes, I did! And you are welcome!'
Am I?! And was it your idea to postpone the wedding?!'
Umm\xc2\x85'
I\xc2\x92m gonna go to the bathroom.'
Wait up! (They both run to the bathroom.)'
Hey-hey, since you\xc2\x92re the \xc2\x91fix-it\xc2\x92 lady, here\xc2\x92s a\npickle, what do you do when the bride says she doesn\xc2\x92t want to have the wedding at\nall?'
She said that?!'
Yeah.'
Why?!'
I don\xc2\x92t know, I told her it was stupid to put off the wedding just\nbecause the hall was gone and she liked flipped out.'
Oh my God. You\xc2\x92re even dumber than I am!'
Excuse me?'
Ross, how long have you been planning this wedding?'
I don\xc2\x92t know. A month?'

Emily has probably been planning it since she was five! Ever since the
first time she took a pillowcase and hung it off the back of her head. That\xc2\x92s what we
did! We dreamed about the perfect wedding, and the perfect place, with the perfect
four-tiered wedding cake (Starting to cry), with the little people on top. (Ross gets
thrown a box of Kleenex from the bathroom and he gives her one.) Thanks. But the most
important part is that we had the perfect guy who understood just how important all that
other stuff was.'
I had no idea. And that-that pillowcase thing, I thought you guys were\njust doing the flying nun.'
Sometimes we were.'
Come on. You gotta help me figure out what to do. Okay?'
Okay.'
Come on. (They leave and Chandler sticks his head out.)'
That was pretty intense huh?'
Yeah. (Pause) Hey, I hope Ross didn\xc2\x92t think that we just went in\nthere because we were uncomfortable being out here!'
(glares at him) I hope he did!'
Hello.'
(on phone) Hey, Pheebs! It\xc2\x92s Joey!'

Hey, Joey! Hey! Ooh! Ooh! I just say someone on the\xc2\x97that looks just\nlike you on the subway. And I was gonna go over and say \xc2\x91hi!\xc2\x92 but then I\nfigured, he doesn\xc2\x92t care if he looks like you.'
That just cost me four bucks. But uh listen, I just called to see how the\nchick and the duck are doing?'
Ohh, they\xc2\x92re having a great time with their Aunt Phoebe!\nAunt Rachel hasn\xc2\x92t been helpful at all. So, do you miss me?'
Kinda, but I\xc2\x92ve just been having way too much fun.'
So you\xc2\x92re not homesick yet?'
No, I don\xc2\x92t think so.'
All right, the seven of us miss you.'
Who\xc2\x92s seven?'
Y\xc2\x92know, me, Rachel, the birds, the babies\xc2\x85'
Ahh, the babies miss me?'
Ooh, the pizza guy\xc2\x92s here!'
What? You ordered pizza without me?!'
Yeah. But y\xc2\x92know we were thinking about you, y\xc2\x92know we ordered\nthe Joey Special.'
Two pizzas?!'
Yep! Okay, gotta go, talk to you later.'
Wait, well, where did you get it from?! '
Monica, why have you brought me here of all places?!'
You\xc2\x92ll see.'
I tell you, this wedding is not going to happen.'
Oh God.'
Okay? But-but imagine a lot more lights, okay? And-and y\xc2\x92know fewer\nbricks, and-and-and flowers, and candles\xc2\x85'
And the musicians, look, they can go over here (Points to a little\nalcove), okay? And the chairs can face this way (Points), and\xc2\x85 (Points to Ross) You\ngo.'
But-but, if you don\xc2\x92t love this, we\xc2\x92ll do it in any other place\nat any other time. Really, it\xc2\x92s fine, whatever you want.'
It\xc2\x92s perfect.'
And, I don\xc2\x92t know, if it starts to rain\xc2\x85'
Well then we\xc2\x92ll get wet. (They kiss.)'
Ohh. And I don\xc2\x92t even have a date.'
Pheebs?'
Yeah?'
Do you remember where the duck food is?'
Yeah, it\xc2\x92s in the guys\xc2\x92 apartment under the sink. Why?'
(enters with a bag packed) Because I\xc2\x92m going to London.'
What?! What do you mean you\xc2\x92re going to London?'
Yeah, I have to tell Ross that I love him. Now honey, you take care, you\ndon\xc2\x92t have those babies until I get back. (Kisses her stomach.) '
I\xc2\x97Rachel, you can\xc2\x92t go! Ross loves Emily!'
Yeah, I know, I know, I know he does. But I have to tell him how I feel!\nHe deserves to have all the information and then he can make an informed decision.'
That\xc2\x92s not why you\xc2\x92re going! You\xc2\x92re going because you\nhope he\xc2\x92s gonna say, "Yeah, I love you too, Rach. Forget that British\nchippy."'
Ohh\xc2\x97Do you think he will?!'

No! Because he\xc2\x92s in love with the British chippy! Look, Rachel, if
you go, you\xc2\x92re just gonna mess with his head and ruin his wedding! Y\xc2\x92know,
it\xc2\x92s too late! You missed you\xc2\x92re chance! I\xc2\x92m sorry, I know this must be
really hard, it\xc2\x92s over.'
Y\xc2\x92know what? No. It\xc2\x92s not over until someone says, "I\ndo." (Exits)'
I do! I do! I do! (Chases her into the hall, but Rachel doesn\xc2\x92t\nstop.) I do! (Gives up.) Ugh, like I can really chase you. I\xc2\x92m carrying a litter.'
Oh...yes..is this..umm..Emily\xc2\x92s Parents\xc2\x92 house.'
Miss Waltham, is at the rehearsal dinner and it\xc2\x92s not polite\nto make fun of people. Goodbye.'
Joey, it\xc2\x92s been three days, okay.. Your just a little homesick,\nOkay. Would you just try to relax. Just, just try to enjoy yourself.'
Hey. I spent the night out. I met this cute bridesmaid. She is so...'
